---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="About"
  description="What this starter is, why it exists, and how to use TNMS Ship to maintain your site."
  headline="About this template"
  accentWord="this template"
  accentColor="cyan"
  eyebrow="About"
  subheadline="ship-a-website is a white-label Astro 6 starter wired for governed AI-assisted maintenance via TNMS Ship."
>
  <section data-variant="paper">
    <div class="section__inner section__inner--prose">
      <div class="prose prose-zinc max-w-none">
        <h2>What is this?</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>ship-a-website</strong> is an open-source starter that shows you how to build and
          maintain a static marketing site using the
          <a href="https://tnms.ai">TNMS Ship</a> agentic pipeline. It is not a UI kit — it is a
          complete, opinionated project skeleton with the guard-rails already installed.
        </p>

        <h2>What's included</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Astro 6</strong> static site generator — zero client JS by default</li>
          <li><strong>Tailwind CSS v4</strong> CSS-first config, all tokens in <code>global.css</code></li>
          <li><strong>BEM enforcement</strong> — ESLint + Stylelint plugins; no inline styles, no raw class names</li>
          <li><strong>SEO lint gate</strong> — keyword registry, offline Tier 1 coverage check, optional SERP audit</li>
          <li><strong>Self-hosted fonts</strong> — Inter Variable, Inter Tight Variable, JetBrains Mono</li>
          <li><strong>Git hooks</strong> — pre-commit SEO gate via <code>.githooks/pre-commit</code></li>
          <li><strong>Ship pipeline</strong> — <code>AGENTS.md</code> + pipeline config for TNMS Ship</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Using TNMS Ship to maintain this site</h2>
        <p>
          Once you have the site up and running, you can connect it to TNMS Ship for governed,
          AI-assisted content and code updates. The pipeline will:
        </p>
        <ol>
          <li>Receive a feature request (new blog post, page update, SEO fix)</li>
          <li>Run the specify → plan → implement → review → merge stages</li>
          <li>Gate every PR on the SEO lint check and BEM enforcement</li>
          <li>Require a human approval before merge to main</li>
        </ol>

        <h2>Customising</h2>
        <p>
          Start with <code>scripts/site.config.ts</code> — set your brand name, URL, and author.
          Then update the placeholder copy in <code>src/layouts/Layout.astro</code> and
          <code>src/components/SiteMark.astro</code>. Finally, add your own keywords to
          <code>src/seo/keywords.ts</code> to activate the SEO lint gate.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
